## Freakonomics Radio


### Freakonomics


* ["Outjargoning" with Lagrange Multipliers in advertising](/assets/podcasts/excerpts/vlc-record-2021-01-03-11h04m45s-Does Advertising Actually Work_Part 2_Digital.mp3)  
(https://freakonomics.com/podcast/advertising-part-2/ 07:20-09:47), **careful, you will laugh out loud!**

* [Tim Wong on AI subsidized by the advertising industry](/assets/podcasts/excerpts/vlc-record-2021-01-03-11h17m02s-Does Advertising Actually Work_Part 2_Digital.mp3)  
(https://freakonomics.com/podcast/advertising-part-2/ 35:24-39:05)

* [Darrick Hamilton on the wealth gap and risk taking](/assets/podcasts/excerpts/vlc-record-freak-Should-America-and-FIFA-Pay-Reparations-2821-2942.mp3)  
(https://freakonomics.com/podcast/reparations-part-1/ 28:21-29:42)

* [America’s outdated math curriculum](/assets/podcasts/excerpts/vlc-record-freak-America’s Math Curriculum Doesn’t Add Up-2501-2732.mp3)  
(https://freakonomics.com/podcast/math-curriculum/ 25:01-27:32)

### People I (Mostly) Admire

* [Kerwin Charles on Public Speaking](/assets/podcasts/excerpts/vlc-record-2021-01-02-15h08m18s-Kerwin Charles_ “One Does Not Know Where an Insight Will Come From”-.mp3)  
(https://freakonomics.com/podcast/pima-kerwin-charles/ 05:45-07:27)

The following semi serious quotes are from a bonus episode introducing the new podcast [People I (Mostly) Admire](https://freakonomics.com/pima/) which can  actually be [watched](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vbGMWZYuCt4&feature=youtu.be) instead of just listened to.

* Steven Levitt on 
  * [avoiding time commitments :)](/assets/podcasts/excerpts/vlc-record-Steve Levitt_I'm Not as Childlike as I'd Like to Be-0125-0156.mp3)  
(https://freakonomics.com/podcast/pima-bonus-steve-levitt/ 01:25 - 01:56)
  * [the folly of getting a PhD or writing books](/assets/podcasts/excerpts/vlc-record-Steve Levitt_I'm Not as Childlike as I'd Like to Be-0338-0520.mp3)  
(https://freakonomics.com/podcast/pima-bonus-steve-levitt/ 03:38 - 05:20)  
I actually do not agree with this extremely oversimplified -borderline pretentious- view whose main purpose seems to want to support Levitt's "iconoclastic" status; but I like it as a thought provoking exercise.

